.SS "WiredTiger release 2\&.6\&.1, 2015-05-13 "
.PP
The WiredTiger 2\&.6\&.1 release contains new features, minor API changes and bug fixes\&.
.PP
New features:
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Move the sync configuration setting from \fBWT_SESSION::begin_transaction\fP to \fBWT_SESSION::commit_transaction\fP\&. Change the setting from a boolean to a string\&. See upgrading documentation for more information\&. refs \fCWT-1908\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add the ability to flag a transaction to be flushed asynchronously on commit via a new sync=[background] configuration option\&. Add a new \fBWT_SESSION::transaction_sync\fP API to wait for asynchronous flushes to complete\&. refs \fCWT-1908\fP, #1943
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add the ability to create a named in-memory snapshot via a new \fBWT_SESSION::snapshot\fP API\&. refs \fCWT-1839\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add the ability to disable write ahead logging at a per-table granularity\&. Accessed via log=(enabled) configuration for \fBWT_SESSION::create\fP API\&. Partial logging has serious implications for recovery, it should be used with caution\&. refs #1989
.PP
.PP
Other noteworthy changes:
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix several bugs related to syncing files for checkpoint durability\&. refs \fCWT-1944\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a segfault during checkpoint where we could attempt to access a file that was in the process of being dropped in the background\&. refs \fCSERVER-18014\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a segfault during eviction where we could attempt to evict a page from a tree that was in the process of being dropped in the background\&. refs \fCSERVER-18460\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug where WiredTiger could segfault in a workload with lots of cache pressure\&. refs \fCWT-1937\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a performance issue with \fBWT_SESSION::compact\fP, where it would spend a long time compacting tables that had no space to reclaim\&. refs \fCWT-1953\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug where accessing an overflow item could return WT_NOTFOUND incorrectly\&. The issue was related to an invalid transaction visibility check\&. refs \fCWT-1745\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Improve performance and avoid changing files on startup if no recovery is required by avoiding the creation of unnecessary checkpoints and log records for files that haven't changed\&. refs \fCWT-1936\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Improve how we handle create of a table, if a file with the same name already exists (possibly from an earlier failed create)\&. refs #1974
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix compiler warnings for LZ4 implementation on Windows\&. refs #2006
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug in the WiredTiger command line utility where it could create a base configuration file for an existing database, if there had been a crash while creating the database\&. refs \fCWT-1943\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a build problem where recent versions of RedHat would fail to detect posix_memalign presence correctly\&. refs \fCWT-1951\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix several problems with how we create, recover and backup databases\&. Related to order of creation and differences between Windows and POSIX file system semantics\&. refs #1993
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug where we could flush the log file more often than required if using auto-commit transactions\&. refs \fCWT-1949\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a performance problem in LSM, where trees created with an initial bulk load could choose poor merges\&. refs \fCWT-1947\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Improve how we decide whether to deepen a tree during an internal split operation\&. Append workloads could create trees that were excessively deep\&.
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug in LSM which could lead to a hang on connection close\&. refs \fCWT-1935\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Fix a bug in the internal random number generator, where concurrent calls could lead to invalid sequences\&. Never seen in the wild\&.
.PP
.PP
.SS "WiredTiger release 2\&.6\&.0, 2015-05-13 "
.PP
The WiredTiger 2\&.6\&.0 release contains new features, minor API changes and many bug fixes\&.
.PP
New features:
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add support for 'at rest' encryption of WiredTiger databases via a new encryption API\&. refs \fCWT-1822\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add support for bulk load in LSM trees (previously the bulk configuration for cursor create was ignored by LSM trees)\&. refs \fCSERVER-18321\fP, \fCWT-1922\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add enhanced compression support for LZ4\&. Change is not compatible with tables created with LZ4 compression using earlier versions of WiredTiger\&. See the upgrading documentation for more information\&.
.PP
.PP
API and behavior changes:
.PP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Enhance performance of \fBWT_SESSION::drop\fP with force enabled (mark the table as dead and discard it in the background without writing any content to disk, rather than flushing content from the cache)\&. refs \fCWT-1894\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Add an API to validate configuration strings\&. refs \fCWT-1739\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Disallow the cache_resident flag on LSM trees\&. refs \fCWT-1905\fP
.IP "\(bu" 2
Enhance the controls for how aggressively idle handles are closed, update the wiredtiger_open file_manager configuration options to expose that control\&. refs \fCSERVER-17907\fP, \fCWT-1856\fP
.PP
.PP
